[{'comment_id': 453250476, 'comment_body': "Let's remove the least amount of things from this list, starting with `stream_socket_client`, and not just the whole line (unless the whole line is necessary to have things work?).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 0, 42, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453250616, 'comment_body': 'why remove the inline type hints?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 0, 44, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453251014, 'comment_body': 'i added those type hints in the annotation right above the function, thought that was enough then. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 0, 49, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'marwanatef2', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453251533, 'comment_body': "It's not, and we should be having inline types as much as possible, especially new classes / files, where we can do `declare(strict_types=1);` at the top, like here. If a file is declared strict, calling a function with the wrong argument types will cause an error to be raised if you call the function with the wrong types (and if you have the inline types but not strict typing, PHP will try and silently coerce types which I dislike).

See [this doc](https://www.php.net/manual/en/functions.arguments.php#functions.arguments.type-declaration.strict) for more info on strict typing.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 0, 57, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453252156, 'comment_body': 'will add inline type declaration.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 12, 1, 6, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'marwanatef2', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 453606193, 'comment_body': 'Please add documentation and type hints for this function.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 13, 12, 15, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kevin-MM', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462044923, 'comment_body': 'I think this line should just be removed, I dont see a reason to keep it in the code but commented out.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 29, 5, 21, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'elihschiff', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462275149, 'comment_body': 'oh yeah, i just forgot to remove it', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 29, 12, 54, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'marwanatef2', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462384595, 'comment_body': 'Travis is failing as this function is still used in one other place. Should we be keeping this function then, or refactor the one place using it?

