> ------ --------------------------------------------------------------- 
>```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 29, 15, 23, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462409306, 'comment_body': 'this function is not called any more, i just forgot to remove it', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 29, 15, 57, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'marwanatef2', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462972180, 'comment_body': 'I think we should have `ws://127.0.0.1:41983/` written as a constant, made to be a global or environmental variable, or otherwise made so we only define it in one single place in the PHP codebase.  I think ideally we would have this value read from the apache2 submitty.conf at some point during installation and made available to PHP code via a `$this->core->getConfig()` method.  I can imagine it will be used many times as more code is written that has the PHP website application interacting with the websocket server.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 30, 12, 50, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kevin-MM', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462985715, 'comment_body': 'Are there any security implications of this?  Would it be possible for a bad actor to fake their user agent to be `websocket-client-php` and gain authorization to the websocket server?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 30, 13, 13, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kevin-MM', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 462988855, 'comment_body': 'Please remove the line break.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 30, 13, 18, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kevin-MM', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 463019632, 'comment_body': "While I agree with this, within this PR, let's just abstract this into making a new class under `site/app/libraries/socket/Client.php` which is (roughly):

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace app\libraries\socket;

use app\libraries\Core;

class Client extends \WebSocket\Client {
    public function __construct(Core $core) {
        parent::__construct('ws://127.0.0.1:41983/', [
            'headers' => [
                'Session-Secret' => $core->getConfig()->getSecretSession()
            ]
        ]);
    }
}
```

for now. I'll write-up an issue later on today (or this week) that details configuration settings for the client, and that can be strictly dealt with in an independent PR.
", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 30, 14, 3, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 463024686, 'comment_body': "Yes. This has security implications. Using the above code, we should validate that if the user_agent is `websocket-client-php` and that `$request->getHeader('Session-Secret')[0] === $this->core->getConfig()->getSecretSession()`. We could also remove the check on user_agent and leave only the latter, but I see no reason to remove it at the moment.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 30, 14, 10, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'MasterOdin', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 463595855, 'comment_body': "Would it be appropriate to add an `else { return false; }` here?  I imagine the php-client doesn't have a cookie set and I'm just wondering if its possible we might end up trying to run functions on null values and result in an exception.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 31, 12, 59, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kevin-MM', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 463648538, 'comment_body': 'yeah, makes sense', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 31, 14, 35, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'marwanatef2', 'type': 'User'}]
